                            <ul class="list-unstyled">
                                <li><i class="ri-check-double-line"></i> <b>Screening and Assessment:-</b> Once the applications are received, the screening process begins. Resumes and cover letters are reviewed, and candidates who meet the initial requirements are shortlisted. Further assessment methods such as interviews, skill tests, aptitude tests, and reference checks may be conducted to evaluate the candidates' suitability for the position.</li>

                                <li><i class="ri-check-double-line"></i> <b>Selection and Offer:- </b> 
                                    The final selection is made based on the candidate's performance during the screening and assessment stages. An offer is extended to the chosen candidate, including details about salary, benefits, and other employment terms. Negotiations may occur during this stage.</li>
                                <li>
                                    <i class="ri-check-double-line"></i> <b>Onboarding:-</b>
                                    After the candidate accepts the offer, the onboarding process begins. This involves completing necessary paperwork, introducing the new employee to the organization's policies and culture, providing orientation, and assigning initial tasks.
                                </li>
                                <li>
                                    <i class="ri-check-double-line"></i> <b>Integration and Retention:- </b>
                                    Once the employee starts working, it is important to ensure their smooth integration into the company. This involves ongoing support, training, and development opportunities to help them succeed in their role. Retention strategies, such as providing a positive work environment, career growth opportunities, and competitive compensation, are crucial to retain top talent in the long run.
                                </li>
                            </ul>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

